Southern weekend intern, he Peiyun

Editor in chief | Wu Xiaoyu, Henin Ho

It's easy to get lost in a hospital like this. Buildings outside the compound are sparse, and if you stray into the courtyard path, there are only trees and grass around. It was snowing in Wuhan in mid February, melting snow into ice and dripping rain from the branches of Chimonanthus Praecox and the pine trees. Occasionally, you can see the Grey Magpie, a small fat bird with a grey back and blue tail that only appears in good places.

This is the designated hospital for the medical treatment of public health emergencies in Wuhan, a hospital for infectious diseases far from downtown Wuhan and a convalescent resort for patients with chronic diseases such as liver disease.

As an Infectious Disease Hospital, Golden Pool has the ability to activate the protection mechanism to deal with infectious diseases as soon as possible, but as a specialist hospital, its own capacity is not enough to face the subsequent influx of critically ill patients.

Starting in December 2019, the gold and Silver Lake became the eye of the storm for the new pneumonia outbreak. Many of the events here predate the Wuhan Urban area, where they were the first to admit patients with severe cases of new coronary pneumonia, the first to vacate their wards, the first to move into foreign aid, and the first to face the danger of "saving one life and one death" .

Today's money is not what it used to be. The most important piece of the puzzle in reorganizing Wuhan's new pneumonia epidemic is the gold and silver pool of the nation's most elite medical forces.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhang Dingyu, director of Wuhan's Golden Pool Hospital, dressed for work, Jan. 29,2020. (Xinhua / Photo)

1
The first patients

1

###The first patients

Much happened on December 30, the first critical day of what became known as the Wuhan outbreak.

At first, the patients did not come one by one, they were sent in droves to the treasure-house.

At 19:00 on December 29,2019, Jiang Wei, a nurse in the intensive care unit (ICU) in Jinyin Tan, received nine patients with pneumonia of unknown cause. They were in the same group, picked up by two cars from different hospitals. One of the relatives, who had followed the patient to the hospital, eagerly told the doctor that he, too, had a fever and might have been infected. He ended up in the hospital, too.

The ICU on the south seventh floor was suddenly told two hours ago to evacuate 14 patients, vacate all 16 beds, disinfect the entire ward, and activate the highest level of level 3 protection. The gold and silver pools are familiar with Level III protection, and they conducted exercises before the 2019 war games against the Middle East respiratory syndrome -- a SARS like coronavirus infection known as Florida. "exactly the same maximum protection, " Jiang said.

Just a few hours ago, the public health departments of Xinhua Hospital and Wuhan Central Hospital of Hubei Province reported to the Disease Control and Prevention Department of Hubei and Wuhan Health Committees that they had treated several patients with "viral pneumonia of unknown cause" . This afternoon, the disease control and Prevention Department of the provincial and Municipal Health and health committees informed the provincial, municipal and district centers for Disease Control and prevention that the above two hospitals treated many pneumonia patients of unknown causes who had a history of exposure to the south China seafood market. They requested that the emergency handling workflow be started. At the same time, jinyintan and two-level Centers for Disease Control and Prevention began epidemiological investigations.

That night, the business vice president of the Golden Pool, Huang Chaolin, took six patients from the Xinhua hospital, and a patient from the Tongji Hospital affiliated to the Chinese University of Science and Technology was transferred to the Golden Pool for pneumonia of unknown cause. Based on the management of infectious diseases, these patients, regardless of their severity, can only be transferred to the ICU, which has been quarantined.

The next day, Dec. 30, was the first critical day of what became known as the Wuhan outbreak.

That day, Dean Zhang Dingyu led the collection of the first seven patients admitted to the Bronchoalveolar lavage and sent it to the Wuhan Virus Institute of the Chinese Academy of Sciences for testing, a key step in understanding pneumonia of unknown causes. Three days later, the institute sequenced the entire genome of COVID-19, and on Jan. 5,2020, the virus strain was isolated.

The South fourth floor was converted into an emergency isolation ward, with the buffer rooms sealed off and all passages turned into one-way passageways. This was originally a common ward that was newly renovated and ready to receive influenza patients (a large number of flu patients were admitted to the Golden Pool that month) . For the next few days, almost every day, a new ward was opened to accommodate patients transferred from the city's hospitals.

Treasure Lake received at least 27 patients on December 30. Twenty-eight Wuhan Medical experts, led by Zhao Jianping, director of respiratory and Critical Care Department of Tongji Hospital, consulted the 27 patients in Jinyintan, 13 of whom were seriously ill. Since then, Zhao Jianping served as Hubei Province Medical Treatment Group leader, led the development of Hubei Province's new crown pneumonia treatment program.

At 4 p.m. that day, 52 beds on the south fourth floor began receiving patients with pneumonia of unknown origin. The head nurse, Liu Ping, and the three nurses stayed up all night, taking in about fifteen patients. When her husband brought his clothes to the hospital, Liu Ping stood at the door of the hospital and cried at him: "I don't think it's as simple as that. "

"although I don't know what it is, but I saw a lot of people's films are white lung. Although I haven't experienced SARS, but I know a little bit. " Mixed emotions, she thought of the medical staff may be in danger.

"seven SARS cases have been confirmed in the south China fruit and seafood market and are being quarantined in the Emergency Department of our hospital, " Li Wenliang, an ophthalmologist at Wuhan Central Hospital, told a group of students on Wechat when Liu Ping was admitted. Li later developed fever and dyspnea in a patient with Glaucoma who was infected with new crown pneumonia. He was diagnosed with new crown pneumonia on January 31 and died 6 days later.

At the same time that the reception for pneumonia of unknown cause began on the fourth floor of the south of Jinyin Lake, at 16:00 on December 30, wuhan Municipal Health Commission should have received all the cases reported by Wuhan Hospitals as a result of the two red-headed documents "on doing a good job in the treatment of pneumonia of unknown cause" and "Municipal Health and Health Commission on the report of pneumonia of unknown cause of emergency notice" sent to various medical institutions, hospitals were asked to compile a list of unidentified pneumonia patients with similar characteristics who had been seen in the last week, and December 30, at 16:00, was the filing time. The three-level Centers for Disease Control and Prevention and control formed the report of Investigation and treatment of many pneumonia cases reported by hospitals in the South China Seafood Market.

Looking back, on December 30th the speed of the response to unexplained pneumonia contrasted sharply with the subsequent outbreak, which was out of control: Many people were standing in front of the alarm bell, but why was it not sounded?

2
Who was the first victim?

2

###Who was the first victim?

On Jan. 9, Lao was officially the first to die, but he was not the first patient to die in a gold and silver lake. Two days ago, 67-year-old Wang passed away in the Golden Pond.

The boss was the first patient to be officially reported to have died of pneumonia of unknown cause.

Old Tseng was in the ICU when he collapsed. 20 days ago, he had a fever, cough, loss of appetite. After four days of difficulty breathing, he was intubated late at night on December 31,2019, and transferred to the gold and silver pool with a suction machine.

The 61-year-old, who spends years sourcing at the South China Seafood Wholesale Market, suffers from chronic liver disease and an abdominal myxoma.

The pool has been staffed by experts from the NHS and Wuhan, who consult on every case in the ICU. The old had been admitted to hospital the next day, the expert group determined that his condition is in a critical stage, mainly to save lives. ECMO treatment is currently available means to strive for conditions for ECMO treatment. ECMO is the most powerful means of in vitro life support, which can temporarily replace the heart and lung function of the patient and buy the time for the patient's heart and lung rehabilitation.

But ECMO can't support organs other than the heart and lungs, which must be able to heal on their own.

In the middle of the night on January 1, Lao was given ECMO, the first patient in the outbreak to be treated with ECMO. In fact, doctors knew that multiple organ dysfunction syndrome was irreversible and could die at any moment. In the days of ECMO, the old appeared bilateral pupil dilate, double lung sound is very weak, several times endangered, by means of first aid pulled back.

A doctor at the central South Hospital who helped with the new pneumonia said they had known from early January that people would die of pneumonia of unknown cause. "there was a patient in the Golden Pool who was dying and just kept turning around with an ECMO, " he said.

Lao Wang was treated at the Union Medical College Cancer Hospital and Union Medical College Hospital. In the week between the two transfers, his lungs went from partially infected to completely white. His sister, daughter and son-in-law began to show symptoms similar to his. Concorde Hospital once organized aspiration specialist consultation, and to the old king intubation rescue, no significant improvement, recommended to be sent to the pool of gold and silver.

On January 7, three days after he was sent to the gold and Silver Lake, Lao Wang died of "severe pneumonia" . The doctor told the family that he was the first patient to die in the outbreak.

On the day of Wang's death, five experts disagreed over the cause of his death. It has been suggested by three experts that pneumonia of unknown cause -- dubbed bacterial pneumonia -- is a clinically common viral pneumonia infection. Two experts believe it is bacterial pneumonia, or that its clinical and imaging features like viral pneumonia, but no etiology, can be ruled out. The final moderator concluded: Severe Pneumonia, with complications such as Acute respiratory distress syndrome, septic shock, and essential hypertension.

At that time, the CDC had not yet provided Wuhan with a PCR NUCLEIC ACID test kit, unable to determine the cause of Lao Wang. After the death of Lao Wang, there were experts and his daughter to communicate whether to carry out an autopsy, but ultimately failed.

Lao Zeng's situation is different. He is the "chosen specimen" .

The next day, he was swabbed for bronchoalveolar lavage fluid. Identifying a COVID-19 that causes severe pneumonia in humans: A descriptive study, published Jan. 27 in the Chinese Medical Journal, one of the samplers was infected with COVID-19.

From the last day of 2019, the first group of patients were admitted to the ICU on the 7th floor of the Golden Pool South. Over the next nine days, the ICU admitted nine patients with severe pneumonia of unknown origin who had been transferred to the hospital. Each patient underwent seven to eight nucleic acid tests, including influenza a, influenza B, Legionella Pneumonia, dengue fever and Adenovirus, to determine whether he or she had a viral infection known to man. Test results showed that all patients admitted to the ICU, the presence of unknown human virus.

At the time, no one knew how many deaths the unknown virus would cause. Zhang Wei, a doctor who has worked in the ICU for 11 years, looks at the patient's CT scan and thinks it looks like H7n9 bird flu. He thought it was nothing more than a raging epidemic with minimal casualties.

"When I first came into contact with these patients, I thought, what's the big deal? It's just bird flu. But then... "

Zhang Wei reported four names, and one by one they died. He did not want to remember that time: "too gray to hear good news. "

As of March 5,2,305 people had died from new crown pneumonia in Wuhan, according to the Department of Health. In the early 2020s, just as outpatient clinics in Wuhan Hospital had not yet realized how contagious the new coronavirus was, so had the Golden Pool of gold and silver not yet realized how cruel the critically ill patients with the new coronavirus were.

3
Open Ward

3

###Open Ward

From December 31 to January 8, all nine patients with pneumonia of unknown cause in the ICU died. The patient with the longest life support was in the ICU for 22 days.

Zhao Jianping was asked by southern weekly to draw a timeline for the development of the epidemic, the first of which he set on Dec. 30 as a gold and silver lake for his first consultation. The second key point was January 10, "when there was a significant increase in the number of patients, and that's when the staff infection started to appear. "

One of the results of the expert consultation is that from January 1, there will be experts at all levels on duty for consultation in the Golden and silver pools, wuhan Health Commission deployed the Wuhan Second Hospital, the Third Hospital, the Fourth Hospital, Wuchang Hospital and other hospitals to support the medical staff.

Even so, at the gold and Silver Lake in early January, many doctors and nurses said it was not clear what kind of epidemic this was. Wuhan City Health Committee that unexplained pneumonia does not exist "person-to-person" , but "person-to-person" speculation has been circulated in the gold and Silver Lake.

ICU Director Wu Wenjuan repeatedly stressed to the department, must do a good job of self-protection. "with more and more patients, we gradually realized that the disease was really different from before. Before, they would only tell us to take good care of it, not so seriously, " said Jiang Wei, a nurse in the ICU.

On January 10, the second time point marked by Zhao Jianping, 16 beds in the ICU of Zhongnan Hospital were full on that day; 30-50 acute and critical patients needed to be hospitalized daily in an emergency center of a third-class hospital. At least five non-ICU wards, each with more than 40 patients, have been filled to the brim. That day, the pool of gold and silver will ICU outside the patients into the mild and severe two categories, classified placement ward.

From 8:00 on January 5 to January 10, the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission did not report the number of people with pneumonia of unknown cause. Since then, from January 11 to January 17, the two sessions of Hubei Province were held in Wuhan. For seven consecutive days, the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission reported no new cases of pneumonia of unknown cause.

And the suburbs of the gold and silver pool ICU, but busy when a person with four people. The nurses pumped them full of hot air, CRRT, and ECMO. The number of machines in the ICU has increased by about twenty, from one CRRT per nurse to four per person at one time.

Each patient needs a constant supply of hyperbaric oxygen, the hospital's existing oxygen supply is not enough, and oxygen tanks are needed. An oxygen tank can only use less than an hour, oxygen delivery master can not come over, the nurses to move their own higher than people oxygen tank. Working until late January, one of the nurses fainted while carrying an oxygen tank at night. The head nurse insisted that she take three days off, but she only took one because there weren't enough hands. So far, ICU has two pregnant nurses, worried about the outbreak of CT or drink Chinese medicine affect the fetus, choose to abort the child.

In a month's time, Gold Silver Tan Hospital 21 floor ward, 3 buildings, all used to treat new coronary pneumonia patients. Four of the general wards were converted into ICU wards.

On the other hand, ICU doctor Zhang Wei was frustrated that these patients were "very special and very different from the previous H7N9 and H1N1 patients. We spent a lot of energy, a lot of hard work and effort, but most of these patients did not get well. ".

Several sources confirmed to southern weekend reporters that from December 31 to January 8, a pool of money ICU income of nine patients with pneumonia of unknown cause died. The patient with the longest life support was in the ICU for 22 days.

4
Isolated island

4

###Isolated island

In early January, the Wuhan Municipal Commission of Health and health offered a plan to support the Golden Pool: Three specialists from each of the seven hospitals with stronger medical capabilities, and ICU nurses from the hospital, will take turns to work in the Golden Pool on a weekly basis.

In mid-january, the gold and silver fields are like an island.

Our hearts must be full of grief .

Cai Yanping is the deputy director of the Second Department of infection doctor. The fourth floor of her complex was asked in mid to early January not to take any more flu patients. Flu Patients Generally five-day discharge cycle, Ward most patients will be discharged, a few patients were transferred to the city Health Commission designated hospitals, continue to receive treatment.

On January 20, she was evacuated from her ward as a recipient of a new pneumonia patient, on January 12, one day after submitting the new coronavirus gene sequence to the World Health Organization Organization, wuhan Municipal Health Commission will be unknown cause of pneumonia COVID-19 infection caused by pneumonia (hereinafter referred to as "new crown pneumonia") .

After the area was cleared, Cai Yanping's department first supported the integrated first floor of the new pneumonia area. She does not know at that time Wuhan epidemic is how to develop, "we do not have outpatient service, can not see particularly chaotic situation" .

To tell the truth, Cai Yanping does not feel physically hard, "the flu in December is also very busy, basically can not rest" , greater suffering from mental stress. In early January, she first heard from a Tongji doctor on the phone that the clinic was already overflowing with fever patients. "If there were so many patients in the clinic, there would be no shortage of The Adventure of the Resident Patient, " she said.

Then she constantly received friends, old classmates, old patients call, asked her to come to see a doctor, to her heart worry.

She gradually found that Wechat is not to see, whether friends or public accounts, are full of sad and even tragic news: Unable to go out, unable to see a doctor, unable to be hospitalized, unable to survive.

Even her best friend, around the Spring Festival, asked her father infected, whether she can be admitted to the hospital, she is powerless. The hard criterion for admission was a positive nucleic acid test, and the best friend's father was slow to pass the nucleic acid test. "If her father had been two weeks late... the criteria had changed, maybe there would have been a way, " the friend told her unwillingly, but the father eventually died at home.

What Cai Yanping did not know was that in the conference room outside her ward, medical experts at the national, provincial and municipal levels were discussing the criteria for judging and diagnosing each day, the viral pneumonia for unexplained pneumonia (trial) and the COVID-19 for pneumonia (trial)(first edition) are the results of hundreds of case discussions based largely on money.

In the first edition of the diagnosis and treatment plan released on January 16, the treatment pointed out that "critical cases should be admitted to the ICU for treatment as early as possible. " However, the follow-up treatment of the epidemic situation could not be carried out according to scientific guidance, and a large number of patients in Wuhan were delayed in treatment due to, in a desperate, desperate situation.

But the progression of the epidemic has made the arrangement ineffective after only one rotation. The number of cases has exploded since January 10. On January 11, Tongji Hospital was the first to deploy Zhong Qiang and four other medical staff with medical equipment to support the gold and Silver Lake. Four days later, the Provincial Health Commission asked Tongji Hospital, Provincial People's Hospital, Union hospital, respectively, take over the south seventh floor, south sixth floor, south fifth floor. All three floors were subsequently converted into intensive care units and staff were deployed from municipal hospitals.

On January 19, the Provincial People's Hospital raised the hope that Hubei Province to form a special ICU team to support Jinyintan. Five days later, the National Health Commission began to draw medical forces from all over the station.

"someone came and came quite a lot, we really feel good to have a sense of dependence, feel safer, " Cai Yanping said. The doctors and nurses of Treasure Lake have done all they can, but they are still far from immune to the spread of the disease.

5
"Oh, my God. "

5

###"Oh, my God. "

He was not in the least pessimistic until he went to the gold and Silver Lake.

Understanding the severity of NCP is like a flashlight beam shining into a dark hole: It allows you to see the most dangerous corner of the epidemic, with a limited view, but enough to plunge you into the dark.

Tongji Hospital Emergency and Critical Care Department Deputy Director Zhong Qiang was the first in the gold and Silver Tan support experts, on duty a week later, he learned that with his partner in the gold and Silver Tan ICU director Wu Wenjuan lung CT showed infection. He went back to Tongji Hospital for a CT scan, which also showed a mild infection.

Fang Minghao will take over from Chung Keung. He was a native of Shandong, bold and direct, and spoke as fast as his mind could move. As deputy director of the Department of Emergency and Critical Care Medicine in Tongji Hospital, Zhong Qiang was appointed to manage the fever clinic in Tongji Hospital in early. At the time, he was running around the hospital, putting out fires, and his wechat steps went from nine thousand sixteen thousand. He didn't think it was serious, "At that time, I just felt that there were a lot more patients with fever. Maybe it was a flu like that, and it passed in a flash. "

At that time he was not pessimistic until he went to the gold and Silver Lake.

When he first arrived, he came into the room and pumped the pump, saying, "there is no carbon dioxide that I can not lower. " This means that their body due to lack of oxygen, carbon dioxide increased, accumulation, affect the normal metabolism of the body's cells and gas exchange. In general, regulating the parameters of breathing -- such as increasing the frequency of breathing, or deep sedation -- can improve the situation to some extent by breathing into the head. But this time, most critical care experts, including Fang Minghao, said the carbon dioxide in the patient's body could not be lowered.

Fang Minghao walked out of the ward and said he was "convinced" . "When I got to the gold and Silver Lake, I finally understood how serious the disease was. I had never seen a patient so serious and so weird in my 20-plus years of serious illness, " he said.

"Hard, very hard, " says at least 10 critically ill patients in Wuhan, who come from different parts of the country. This is both a scientific problem, but also the difficult conditions for treatment.

The Golden Pool was first designated as the new crown pneumonia admission hospital, followed by the Lung Hospital. In the case of the Golden Pool, the strength of the ICU is weak, there are only five doctors, the hospital's various types of oxygen therapy equipment added up to no more than 20. January 21, Fang Minghao took over the first day of the south seventh floor ICU, "the class does not go down. " He described the way.

ICU only two undergraduate room doctors: Zhang Wei and Tu Chao, the other three doctors are on sick leave. There are two emergency transfer of AIDS doctors, two people are mesmerized, sincerely said "we will make doctor's orders, but will not see (this kind) patients, " Fang Minghao recalled. This is the various medical forces to support the epidemic a common phenomenon, non-respiratory or emergency critical care doctors, in the middle of the epidemic is more to play the role of manpower.

The next day, Fang Minghao and National Health Commission experts Du Bin, Tong Zhaohui and Qiu Haibo together rounds. The three experts from the Special Department of Critical Care or respiratory medicine arrived in Wuhan four days ago and were checked into the ICU every day.

Ward rounds start at 8 a.m. , and take more than an hour to go through all the patients'medical records before changing into protective clothing. "every patient has been checked for a long time, and when they come out they say, 'this is no good. 14 patients, if one doctor checks it out, there's no way to control it. Because the patient is so bad, you have to know how bad it is, and 14 patients could die in a day,"Fang said.

The difficulty of ICU care does not depend on the number of patients, depending on the severity of the patient. "these patients, not to mention the medical conditions in Jinyin Tan, were not as heavy even in our previous ICU at Tongji Hospital, where 14 people were all as heavy, " Fang said.

These 14 patients'vital signs are extremely unstable, may look good for one hour, the next hour to rescue. How to use pressors, how to adjust the suction machine, how to balance the intake and output of liquids, whether or not drainage is needed, whether or not anticoagulation is required, chest radiography, blood sampling for biochemical tests, several blood gas analyses, several oral care, etc. , this requires a thorough understanding of the patient and close observation at all times. Even on a normal day, treating two ICU patients can keep a doctor busy.

The reality is, there were only three real ICU doctors in the ward. With 14 patients, a doctor can go into a round of rounds and come out with a handful of patients to forget -- in an infectious disease ward, you can't bring anything in, you can only use your brain for memory. Even with a good memory, a doctor can't plan for every patient well enough.

On the afternoon of the end of rounds, three big experts sitting in the gold and silver pool ICU decided to apply to the National Health Commission, and then send some experts into the gold and silver pool. At least two more specialists in one ward, six or seven under one person, and three or four more doctors under one person for clinical treatment.

The next day, January 23, Jiang Li, director of the Department of Critical Care Medicine at Xuanwu Hospital in Beijing, and Zhong Ming, deputy director of the Department of Critical Care Medicine at Zhongshan Hospital in Shanghai, were both notified to leave for Wuhan immediately.

6
South sixth floor

6

###South sixth floor

"What is the wrong treatment? "

"there was no rescue, " said the bell.

"What is the wrong treatment? "

"there was no rescue, " said the bell.

The South sixth floor has also been converted into an ICU. Jiang Li came here for a month, slowly understand the patients who can persist to survive through what kind of route.

"At first, the hypoxia patients were like a person walking up a cliff, the road was always flat, and when they walked forward, they couldn't see the cliff, and neither could the doctors. By the time the doctors realized, one of his feet had fallen off, " Jiang said.

For 20 days, the doctors with the most deaths could finally see how far the cliff was, knowing they would fall. "But just knowing how it happened and how it developed has not been able to learn to quickly block progress in a particular area. As doctors, we can only monitor him going forward to judge when he is about to fall, and lift him up to see if he can hold, and maybe some people can,"Jiang said.

On the south sixth floor, one of the patients whose bell chimed for the longest time was intubated for more than a month. According to the Bell, the non-invasive aspiration of the patient also depends on their own efforts, the aspirated patient is completely in the hands of the doctor.

In the case of NCP, a three-week battle between the body and the virus determines life and death. "In theory, the patient has survived the battle with the virus, but the previous blow was too much for him, " Zhong said.

Bell would not elaborate, but he revealed that at this time in the ICU, there are many real-life problems that hinder patients' recovery. "It's not the same as the patients we usually have in the ward. "

Could be a lack of manpower. There are more than 20 beds on the sixth floor in the south. The total number of medical staff is about 40. The standard care-to-care ratio in the ICU is 0.5-1 doctor and 3 nurses to a patient. In addition to the south seventh floor ICU, there are four additional ICU wards with only two positive pressure suction hoods in each ward. In the face of such a strong infectious disease, there is not enough strong protective equipment, medical staff can not be guaranteed to be completely safe for sputum suction and other close care.

At the time of the interview, Zhong did not know whether the patient, who had been intubated for more than a month, would recover. In addition to attacking the lungs, the new coronavirus also affects the heart and kidneys, causing systemic multiple organ dysfunction syndrome in the case of underlying disease or old age.

You can feel the urgency of the bell ringing. Sun Yat-sen Hospital colleagues said he preferred the perfect, work hard. ICU doctors are not afraid to face death, the impact on them is unexpected death. "We have seen a lot of patients die in a short period of time, and every single one of them, we have directly or indirectly witnessed a family tragedy, and it has hit us harder than ever. We've been through a lot of battles, seen life and death, but this time it's really different,"Zhong said.

In interviews, doctors at various hospitals described similar sudden deaths: Waking in the morning and dying in the evening; four patients dying in one night, trying to save their lives and watching the next die; the doctor's rounds were over, and he thought everything was fine, when I took off my hazmat suit, one of the ECG monitors behind me went straight.

For some critically ill patients, death is not a slow process, it may be just a moment. Sometimes it feels like I'm stuck in my throat and can't take my last breath, sometimes it feels like I'm in a coma, and the injured cells in different organs can't keep working and collapse at the critical point.

Sudden death. That's not what the ICU doctor would allow. They want to know exactly what each patient is supposed to do at each stage of the illness, and then hold it as long as they can. We learned from the side, Jiang Li and Zhong Ming early take over more than 20 patients, not a recovery.

Jiang Li and Zhong Ming remember every patient. "These patients impressed me so much that I knew I was going to have to learn again, to start over, and that past experiences might not have worked. I have to be very careful with every patient, because it can be completely out of your control. I can no longer give every patient the very right treatment as I used to,"Zhong said.

"Is there a right way or a wrong way to treat it? "

"Yes. You don't know whether it's right or wrong, " the bell said. For example, ending a non-invasive point in time can be a mistake.

Frankly, early arrivals to the gold and silver intensive care unit often leave the doctor feeling passive. Because of the delay in treatment, the patient sent to the Golden Pool, the course of the disease has accelerated into the end stage. "The gold and silver lake bed is open, everything else wants to turn the serious disease, in the operation way you one oxygen can not keep up with, once arrived at the gold and Silver Lake to be heavy, even immortal he also has no good method, " said an ICU doctor. Another doctor directly described the epidemic in the early days, transferred to the hospital gold and silver lake "almost half a dead man came over. ".

The doctors did everything they could, that's for sure. No doctor will do anything wrong subjectively, but the human understanding of the disease's road, the price is a life.

The road "heaped with the experience of many patients dying" is now being blared by Fang Minghao to colleagues who have not come into contact with large numbers of critically ill patients. In order not to let them return to their first day in the gold and Silver Lake, "take a bunch of patients, hesitate for a while, the person is gone. ".

7
Regroup

7

###Regroup

Compared with the whole medical team, the medical unit composed of experts from different places and disciplines may also be divided because of experience and habits.

Today's gold and Silver Lake is a battleground of the nation's top medical forces.

The first national experts to arrive at Jinyin Tan, such as Jiang Li and Zhong Ming, were stationed in the ICU on the 5th, 6th and 7th floors of the south more than 40 days ago. Five "senior" ICU nurses from Xiangya Hospital in Changsha were deployed to support them.

Most of the wards are made up of nearly 300 doctors and nurses from Anhui, Henan, Guangdong and Hubei, and more than 800 doctors and nurses from the hospital.

In addition, Jinyintan currently has the first medical teams in Shanghai, the first medical teams in Fujian and the national traditional Chinese medicine team, which are formed to take over the five wards. The Shanghai Medical Team and the Army Medical University medical team, each with one hundred and forty or so personnel, arrived in the early 1930s and were the first medical units from other provinces to be based in Wuhan. The latter was transferred out after the completion of the Fire God mountain, and the Fujian Medical Team took over its ward.

The first medical teams in Shanghai were composed of respiratory, critical care, infectious and emergency medicine departments. They took over the second floor of the North Building and transformed the third floor into the ICU ward.

This is a huge challenge, Shanghai team captain Zheng Junhua said frankly, "the ICU next risk is very big, but later thought, since it is out of Shanghai, we must have the courage to shoulder the heavy burden. "

In the first week, the Shanghai team relearned and adapted a completely different diagnostic and treatment process, how to use the medical record system, how to check, transfer to the ward, get equipment, supplies and so on. From the General Ward to the three-district Infectious Disease Ward, the work flow also needs to comb. "In my 13 years as dean, I have never used such a high level of sensory control and prevention measures, " said Zheng

In the early days, the Shanghai team encountered many difficulties, such as the exploration of intensive care, as well as the proper management of patients'emotions. And the first problem that they solved, is to continuously reflect to the country and province and city, improve the oxygen supply system of gold and silver pool.

At the time, the Shanghai team had thirty patients in its ward using suction machines. The pool has never treated so many critically ill patients, the original oxygen is not only enough, but also every night at midnight and around seven in the morning, the sudden loss of oxygen.

"All levels have given gold and silver pools the greatest support, but it takes a process, " Zheng said. After the Shanghai team was stationed for two weeks, Jinyin Tan's oxygen supply system was improved. The original 6 cubic meters oxygen supply pipe was changed into more than twice the 15 cubic meters oxygen supply pipe, which solved the problem of unstable breathing caused by unstable oxygen pressure.

Zhang Dingyu, director of the Golden Pool, told southern weekend that 80 percent of the patients in the pool were seriously ill, according to the fifth edition of the diagnosis and treatment plan.

Jinyintan has opened five ICU wards to take over critically ill patients, more than any other hospital in Wuhan. Before that, it was an infectious disease hospital with three seven-story inpatient buildings. Non-invasive aspiration machines, aspiration machines, high-flow oxygen equipment increased tenfold, there are now more than 200 sets. Jiang Li estimates that the amount of medical equipment in the pool of gold and silver "less than, more than under. ".

"Many hospitals have very little breathing. They may not be able to stop the deterioration of the patient. With so many new pneumonia patients in the hospital, their need for oxygen is common, " Jiang said.

Compared with the whole medical team, the medical unit composed of experts from different places and disciplines may also be divided because of experience and habits. Several doctors in Wuhan said that although there were many consultation opinions in a critically ill patient in Jinyintan, the patient died after trying various possibilities on a young patient.

It was a hot day in Wuhan at noon in late February. At the end of the interview, a southern weekend reporter met two discharged patients, a 48-year-old aunt and an 84-year-old grandmother, sitting in the sun by the flower bed, waiting for the community car to come to pick them up.

My aunt began to talk about her experiences at the quarantine point and in the shelter, and suddenly she began to cry. Until she could turn into a pool of gold and silver, she felt "half cured" .

By the early morning of March 5,80,424 cases of NCP had been confirmed, 2,984 people had died, and 6,416 cases of severe NCP had been diagnosed.

Although critical care is still difficult, but for patients with mild and ordinary patients, the new coronavirus is not terrible. According to the latest data provided by the Dean, Zhang Dingyu, the discharge rate at Jinyintan was 59.81% as of the morning of March 4.

"I'm good and have antibodies, right? I'll donate blood when I'm done, " she said.

Liu Ping, Grandpa Wu, Lao Tseng, and Lao Wang are aliases
